Joint sittings of the two houses of Parliament, the National Assembly and National Council of Provinces, is debating the address delivered by Ramaphosa on Thursday. JOHANNESBURG - Members of Parliament (MPs) are continuing the debate of President Cyril Ramaphosa's State of the Nation Address in the National Assembly chamber on Tuesday afternoon. Joint sittings of the two houses of Parliament, the National Assembly and National Council of Provinces, is debating the address delivered by Ramaphosa on Thursday. WATCH LIVE: Sona debate continues 